{
  "texts": [
    "Stained cells were imaged on a Zeiss LSM 710 Spectral Confocal Laser Scanning Microscope (Jena, Germany).",
    "We used a Plan-Apochromat 40x/1.40 or 63×/1.40 Oil DIC objective.",
    "Excitation lasers were 405 nm (for DAPI), 488 nm (for Alexa Fluor 488), and 543 nm (for Alexa Fluor 555).",
    "Emission filter windows were 415-474 (for DAPI), 504-562 (for Alexa Fluor 488), and 504-562 (for Alexa Fluor 555).",
    "Over 100 nuclei per condition were scored for quantification."
  ]
}